Consider the procedure below for the Producer-Consumer problem which uses semaphores:
<pre><code class="c">semaphore n = 0;
semaphore s = 1;
void producer()
{
    while(true)
    {
     produce();
     semWait(s);
     addToBuffer();
     semSignal(s);
     semSignal(n);
    }
}</code></pre>
<pre><code class="c">void consumer()
{
   while(true)
   {
    semWait(s);
    semWait(n);
    removeFromBuffer();
    semSignal(s);
    consume();
   }
}</code></pre>
Which one of the following is <b>TRUE</b>?

A system has n resources R<sub>0</sub>,.....,R<sub>n-1</sub>, and k processes P<sub>0</sub>,.....,P<sub>k-1</sub>. The
implementation of the resource request logic of each process P<sub>i</sub>, is as follows: 
<pre><code>if (i%2==0) {
  if (i &lt; n) request R<sub>i</sub>;
  if (i+2 &lt; n) request R<sub>i+2</sub> ;
}
else {
  if (i &lt; n) request R<sub>n-i</sub>;
  if (i+2 &lt; n) request R<sub>n-i-2</sub>;
}</code></pre>
